result.formatted_address: G/F 18 Hennessy Road, Wan Chai, Hong Kong
result.name: Rempah Noodles

reviews.text: Taste is mild suit to all perhaps. Though spices are packed in but does not taste any hot or spicy at all. The price is a bit high may be cuz on main road Center of town. Only limited choices of noodle provided and are all $98 + $18 for a drink. For such a price one can have 3 course meal plus restaurants service in the vicinity.
Pretty good noodles. Friendly service. Pretty small shop with about four tables.
Staffs were attentive and nice. Dishes were good especially their starters & toast! It was delicious...prawn noodles tasted sweet and portion was perfect! Will try their laksa next time.

Impeccable kaya toast and nonya laksa broth 💯 
Had to queue for 30 mins on a weekday at 1:30
The Laksa is one of the best I had in HK. The place is pretty hipster, for better or for worse. Sitting could be uncomfortable. The staff was nice.

牛𦟌、筋、腩及牛肋條都很林滑，肉味夠濃，麵身有咬口。堅持各款式都帶點辣，有特色！雖然是小店一間，佈置有心思，每碗麵份量也磅過，特別為女仕預備兩條紥起頭髮（避免變了沾麵）用的橡筋，貼心！
Pretty good noodles. Friendly service. Pretty small shop with about four tables.
Staffs were attentive and nice. Dishes were good especially their starters & toast! It was delicious...prawn noodles tasted sweet and portion was perfect! Will try their laksa next time.
有特色，只做三種主食，味道不錯，招呼好。
